cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with establishing dense correspondences between 3D faces, which is a problem in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves triangulation, surface curvature, and level set geodesic curves, which are topics in computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of a deformable model and morphing algorithm suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed algorithms involves quantitative benchmarks, which could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
